Package tekno

Class KnowledgeGraph

java.lang.Object
tekno.KnowledgeGraph
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.AutoCloseable
public class KnowledgeGraph
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.AutoCloseable
This class takes care of the connection with the Neo4J DBMS, handling data inserts and exports from the graph

  • Constructor Details

    • KnowledgeGraph

      public KnowledgeGraph()
      Constructor of the class. It takes no arguments,and if called asks for the parameters, namely URI, user and password on the console log. After inserting the parameters, it instantiates the connection on the private attribute driverNeo4J.

    • KnowledgeGraph

      public KnowledgeGraph​(java.lang.String uri, java.lang.String usr, java.lang.String pwd)
      Constructor of the class. No request will be asked to the user. Automatically create the connection with the database
      Parameters:
      uri - connection string for the database
      usr - user name of the database
      pwd - password of the database

    • KnowledgeGraph

      public KnowledgeGraph​(java.lang.String uri, java.lang.String usr, java.lang.String pwd, java.lang.String xml_source)
      Constructor of the class. No request will be asked to the user. Automatically create the connection with the database, and automatically loads data from an XML file passed in input as String xml_source. This constructor calls another static class called XMLtoKnowledgeGraph.
      Parameters:
      uri - connection string for the database
      usr - user name of the neo4j database
      pwd - password of the neo4j database
      xml_source - the file from witch the db will be created

    • extractFacts

      public void extractFacts​(java.lang.String fileName, java.lang.String folder)
      extracts prolog facts from the current knowledge base stored in the neo4j database.
      Parameters:
      fileName - name of the output file where the facts will be stored
      folder - folder location to which the file will be saved.

    • addNode

      public void addNode​(java.lang.String id, java.lang.String name, java.lang.String type)
      adds a new node to the graph, if not already present. if the node is already present with the isNode method, then after establishing a new Session it performs a query to add a new object to the database, with the specified id, name and type.
      Parameters:
      id - id of the node
      name - name of the node
      type - label or property of the node

    • addNodeProperty

      public void addNodeProperty​(java.lang.String id, java.lang.String type)
      this method adds a property to a specified node, after checking it exists with the isNode method
      Parameters:
      id - id of the node
      type - the property to add to the node

    • getNodeId

      public java.lang.String getNodeId​(java.lang.String name)
      this method returns the id of a node of which name it is specified in input as a String
      Parameters:
      name - the name of the node
      Returns:
      the id of a node of which name it is specified in input as a String, null if a node with the specified name does not exist.

    • addEdge

      public void addEdge​(java.lang.String id1, java.lang.String id2, java.lang.String type)
      this method adds a new edge in the graph between two nodes, specified by id, with the specified type property. First it checks if both nodes exist, then checks if the same edge is not already present. If this condition is satisfied, it runs a query to add the edge to the knowledge base.
      Parameters:
      id1 - id of the node from where the edge starts
      id2 - id of the node from where the edge ends
      type - the label of the edge

    • isNode

      public java.lang.Boolean isNode​(java.lang.String id)
      this method checks, with a query, if the node with the id specified in input, is already present in the knowledge base. It returns true if it exists, false otherwise.
      Parameters:
      id - id of the node to check
      Returns:
      true if the node is in the graph, false otherwise

    • isEdge

      public java.lang.Boolean isEdge​(java.lang.String id1, java.lang.String id2, java.lang.String type)
      this method checks, with a query, if an edge between two specified nodes with the respective ids specified in input, is already present in the knowledge base.
      Parameters:
      id1 - id of the node from where the edge starts
      id2 - id of the node from where the edge ends
      type - the label of the edge
      Returns:
      true if a connection of the specified type exists, false otherwise.

    • resetGraph

      public java.lang.Boolean resetGraph()
      this method deletes all nodes and edges from the current instance of the knowledge base.
      Returns:
      true if success, false otherwise

    • close

      public void close() throws java.lang.Exception
      this method is used to close the connection with the neo4J database, calling the method close() on the driver private attribute.
